data.text:
Public Power Coloring Contest

The Grand Haven Board of Light & Power is throwing a coloring contest for all budding artists in grades one through four! Join the fun and help us light up Public Power Week from Oct. 6-12. Let's celebrate alongside over 2,000 other superhero-like, community-driven electric utilities, shining a light on 49 million Americans. Our Public Power Coloring Contest aims to spark excitement and knowledge about how electricity powers up our awesome community! Let's color our way to a brighter future together!
